  "issue_number": 692,
  "issue_title": "[BUG] --json CLI commands emit ANSI-styled text on stdout when they fail",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`gitt issues bounty-pool --json`, `gitt issues pending-harvest --json`, `gitt admin info --json`, and `gitt vote list --json` emit Rich-formatted red ANSI text on stdout when they fail, instead of structured JSON. Callers running `json.loads(stdout)` get `JSONDecodeError` instead of `{\"success\": false, \"error\": ...}`.\n\nPR #660 fixed the success path for these commands. The exception paths still call `print_error(str(e))` directly (or via `_handle_command_error` from #504), ignoring `--json`.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n    $ gitt issues bounty-pool --json --rpc-url ws://unreachable:9944\n    \u2717 <ANSI-red connection error>\n    $ echo $?\n    1\n\n`json.loads(stdout)` fails.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\n    {\"success\": false, \"error\": {\"type\": \"cli_error\", \"message\": \"<reason>\"}}\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nRed ANSI text on stdout, no JSON.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Ubuntu 24.04\n- Python: 3.12.3\n- Commit: db585db\n\n## Additional Context\n\nThe helper `handle_exception(as_json, ...)` already exists in `helpers.py:216` (from #231) and is used correctly by `submissions.py`. Fix is to route the four exception handlers through it.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-23T15:14:38.000Z",
  "test_cmd": [
